Colores is 7 years old today! 7 years ago in early June I convinced my husband to go to Morocco the following month in hopes of finding the holy grail of straw bags purveyors. We booked the trip and what ensued was a week long history class of Morocco, its people and their incredible gifts and talents. After several years of hand painting more than 4,000 bags, I decided we had to find bags and a business model that didn’t require personalization for every sale. Enter, le bucket bag! Made in Italy, but a mixture of raffia and leather, it was the perfect addition to our Colores family, and so the journey will continue as we cultivate new styles or bags and items for you to love. 
We’ve had many failures, lots of successes but most of all, countless moments of witnessing the power of women and businesses coming together to the most create community.
From Houston to Atlanta, 30A to Aspen, London to Palm Beach, I’ve sat in stores, shops, streets and just about anywhere else they would let me pop up. In the course of 7 years I’ve witnessed a lot of businesses hang up their hats, while others have rocketed to superstardom. I feel honored to still be here all these years later and look forward to another 7, God willing. So thank you for joining in on this ride, I can promise it won’t be boring!

For the last several days I’ve been thinking of the perfect thing to say and I’ve realized the perfect words or time don’t exist. It’s incomprehensible that this level of hate and evil can take hold in our world, putting the worst of man on display, as we watch in horror from afar. 
Evil that takes innocent lives, especially those of women and children should have no place on our earthly residence. What does have a righteous place here? LOVE. Love for thy neighbor, love for those we disagree with, love for those we don’t understand. Our prayers are with Israel and all those affected by this evil. May love conquer all! 🤍 🇮🇱
